cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with broadcasting capabilities in LTE networks. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the scheduling of broadcasting sessions affects multiple contiguous cells. Additionally, it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper presents a model and algorithms for content scheduling. It may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as broadcasting is a common method for delivering multimedia content. Finally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper discusses the trade-offs between effectiveness and computational efficiency in scheduling.
